#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. What's new since 2.2.X-RELEASE\n"
"---------------------------------\n"
"All changes described here are unique to the 3.0 branch unless\n"
"specifically marked as [MERGED] features.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.1. KERNEL CHANGES\n"
"-------------------\n"
"o The 2.2.x SCSI subsystem has been almost entirely replaced with\n"
"  a new \"CAM\" (Common Access Method) SCSI system which offers\n"
"  improved performance, better error recovery and support for more\n"
"  SCSI controllers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The Host ATM Research Platform (\"HARP\") software by Network\n"
"  Computing Services, Inc. has been integrated into the system.\n"
"  See /usr/src/share/examples/atm for more info.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The SMP (Symmetric MultiProcessing) branch has been merged.\n"
"  The kernel is mostly non-reentrant as yet, but work is under way.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "o The code from 4.4BSD-Lite2 has been (finally) merged.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "o Secure RPC is now supported (and usable with NFS et al).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "o Sun's WEBNFS standard is now supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The MSDOS filesystem code now handles VFAT and FAT32 partitions.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.7 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "o ATAPI/IDE CD burner support (BETA).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "o ATAPI/IDE tape drive support (BETA).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Support for using VESA video modes. It is now possible to select and\n"
"  use the modes provided by the BIOS on modern videocards. This enables\n"
"  fx. 132x60 sized consoles and highres graphics in a generic manner on\n"
"  hardware that supports it. There is also support for running the\n"
"  console in rastermode, which allows XFree86 to run a simple 16color\n"
"  server in 800x600 on otherwise unsupported video hardware.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "o Support for AdvanSys SCSI controllers\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "o Support for QLogic SCSI and Fibre Channel controllers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Support for Adaptec 7890, 7891, 7895, 7896 and 7897 based controllers\n"
"  (new 2940/2950/3940/3950 et al).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The ed0 (wd8xxxx, 3c503, NE2000, HP Lan+) Ethernet device's default IRQ\n"
"  has changed from IRQ 5 to IRQ 10.\n"
"  The ed1 Ethernet device has been removed.  Use the Userconfig utility\n"
"  to change ed0's values to match your network card's settings.\n"
"  [MERGED: Both changes are in 2.2.6 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE "
"branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The code responsible for maintaining time of day has been\n"
"  rewritten.  New features are:  true support for nanoseconds in\n"
"  both kernel and userland, continuous rather than stepwise adjustment\n"
"  by NTPD and support for synchronizing to high precision external time\n"
"  signals.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Support for the PPS API described in draft-mogul-pps-api-02.txt for\n"
"  TTL rising edge inputs via the parallel printer port has been added\n"
"  to the printer driver.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Use the new if_multiaddrs list for multicast addresses rather than the\n"
"  previous hackery involving struct in_ifaddr and arpcom.  Get rid of the\n"
"  abominable multi_kludge.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:125
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The new if_media selection method for ethernet drivers has been brought\n"
"  in, obtained from Jason Thorpe's implementation for NetBSD.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.5 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Multi-session ISO-9660 CD-ROMs are now fully supported.  By default, the\n"
"  last session will be mounted (including for root mounts).  For non-root\n"
"  mounts, mount_cd9660(8) can take an argument to mount a particular\n"
"  session instead of the default one.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The UPAGES are gone from the per-process address space which allows\n"
"  complete address space and page table sharing by reference count.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Newly forked child processes return directly to user mode rather than\n"
"  return up through the fork() syscall tree.  This eliminates the kernel\n"
"  stack copy at fork time and simplifies certain other internal "
"operations.\n"
"  It is also needed to support the removal of the UPAGES.  (The idea for\n"
"  this originally came from NetBSD, but we did it for different reasons.)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o vfork() is now fully functional by taking advantage of the new sharing\n"
"  semantics and a significant speedup has been measured.  This can be\n"
"  disabled via the kern.fast_vfork sysctl variable in case of problems.\n"
"  Statically linked binaries from older releases and other BSD platforms\n"
"  are a problem since there was a bug in the 4.4BSD (net2, Lite and Lite2)\n"
"  popen() implementation.  rfork() also has access to these facilities,\n"
"  intended for supporting kernel assisted threads.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:151
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o With the contribution of Berkeley Software Design, Inc., Jonathan "
"Lemmon,\n"
"  Mike Smith, Sean Eric Fagan, and John Dyson, VM86 support has been added\n"
"  to the kernel, and BSD/OS's contributed doscmd has been ported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:155
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The SA_NOCLDWAIT flags has been implemented, featuring the System V\n"
"  option where a process can express its wish to never get zombies or\n"
"  SIGCHLD for dead children.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o An implementation of poll(2) is in place, the core of which is derived\n"
"  from the NetBSD implementation.  Both the select() and poll() syscalls\n"
"  use the poll device, file and vnode ops routines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o An implementation of issetugid(2) that is similar to the OpenBSD call\n"
"  of the same name.  We set the flag in more cases than OpenBSD - our\n"
"  implementation is slightly more paranoid.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Async IO is implemented (under non-SMP at this stage) with additional\n"
"  support for kernel assisted threads.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Some other misc syscalls for compatability with other systems: "
"getsid(2),\n"
"  setpgid(2), nanosleep(2).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o A new syscall signanosleep(2) which is like nanosleep(2), but a specific\n"
"  signal mask is used to determine which signals will wake the sleep.  In\n"
"  a nutshell this is 'wait for a given set of signals for up to a certain\n"
"  amount of time'.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o sleep(3) and usleep(3) are now implemented in terms of signanosleep(2)\n"
"  and now have correct SIGALRM interaction semantics and sleep(3) "
"correctly\n"
"  returns the time remaining.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:181
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o An in-kernel linker is implemented and intended to replace the lkm "
"system\n"
"  and the bogosity that goes with it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o All supported network protocols have been updated to avoid the ``big\n"
"  switch'' pr_usrreq(), and to pass a process pointer down to each user\n"
"  request that might need process credentials or want to sleep,\n"
"  replacing the previous hodgepodge of inspecting curproc (which only\n"
"  occasionally did the right thing) and the SS_PRIV socket state flag.\n"
"  The latter has now been eliminated, along with the SO_PRIVSTATE socket\n"
"  option which cleared it.  Protocols are now also given the opportunity\n"
"  to override the generic send, receive, and poll routines, which will\n"
"  make it possible for a more efficient, protocol-specific\n"
"  implementation of these entry points in later releases.  Finally, many\n"
"  parts of the network code have been modified to cease storing socket\n"
"  addresses and other metainformation in mbufs, in preparation for the\n"
"  eventual elimination thereof.  The mechanism by which socket addresses\n"
"  are now returned is still highly subject to change as we experiment to\n"
"  discover the most efficient method.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:201
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Responses to multicast ICMP ECHO REQUEST (``ping'') and ADDRESS MASK\n"
"  REQUEST packets can now be disabled via sysctl.  The netstat program\n"
"  will print out statistics on how many times this happens.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "o A subtle and seldom encountered bug in ffs has been fixed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The VFS name cache has been reworked to be more accountable and "
"efficient.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:208
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The generic part of VOP_LOOKUP() has been put it in system-wide function\n"
"  which filesystems can rely on for the canonical stuff.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:211
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Vnode freelist handling has been hauled over.  Vnodes are only on the\n"
"  freelist if nobody cares about them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:214
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The kernel provides assistance to getcwd() from data stored in the name\n"
"  cache if possible.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o An interrupt driven configuration hook mechanism has been implemented.\n"
"  This allows drivers to postpone part of their configuration until after\n"
"  interrupts are fully enabled.  This speeds booting because busy-waiting\n"
"  is avoided for things like sub device probing (eg: SCSI bus probes).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:224
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The timeout(9) system in the kernel has been overhauled.  This gives\n"
"  O(1) insertion and removal of callouts and an O(hash chain length)\n"
"  amount of work to be performed in softclock.  The original paper is at:\n"
"        http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/~amc/research/timer/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:228
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Changes in driver buffer queuing to deal with ordered transactions.  "
"This\n"
"  is intended for sequencing data and metadata writes in the filesystem "
"code\n"
"  once fully supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:231
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o EISA Shared interrupts are now supported, working with the framework\n"
"  originally for supporting PCI shared interrupts.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "o Support for the Comtrol Rocketport card.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:238
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o IPFW's packet and byte counters have been expanded from 32 to 64 bits,\n"
"  a `FWD' operation has been added to ipfw to support transparent\n"
"  proxying and the divert operation has changed slightly - see the man\n"
"  pages for natd(8) and ipfw(8) for more information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:243
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o New Plug and Play (PnP) support that allows you to (re)configure PnP\n"
"  devices.  Also support modems being detected by the PnP part and\n"
"  automatically attached.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.6 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Import of new sound code from Luigi Rizzo.  This code is still being\n"
"  developed, but has support for a number of different cards.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.6 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o The psm, mse and sysmouse drivers are improved to provide better mouse\n"
"  support.  In particular, the psm driver now supports various ``wheeled''\n"
"  mice.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.6 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:256
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Added support for SMC EtherPower II 10/100 Fast Ethernet card\n"
"  (aka SMC9432TX based on SMC83c170 EPIC chip).\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.7 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:259
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Added support for ATAPI floppy drives (LS-120).\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.7 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:263
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Added support for IBM Etherjet and other Crystal Semiconductor\n"
"  CS89x0-based NICs.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.7 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:266
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Added support for Texas Instruments TNET100 'ThunderLAN' PCI NIC.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.8 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"o Added full bus master DMA support for 3c900 and 3c905 adapters and\n"
"  added support for the 3c905B.\n"
"  [MERGED: Also in 2.2.8 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:275
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.2. SECURITY FIXES\n"
"-------------------\n"
"[MERGED: all changes soon after specified date in 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:290
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"97/7/29 Lots of lpr/lpd security fixes merged from OpenBSD.\n"
"97/8/22 buffer overflows in tip corrected (benign since tip isn't\n"
"        set[ug]id)\n"
"97/8/26 buffer overflow in glob fixed, no know exploits\n"
"97/8/27 vacation security problem with sendmail corrected (SNI)\n"
"97/8/29 inetd sleeps less when children exit, making DoS attacks much\n"
"        harder.\n"
"97/8/29 fts now race-proof and find -execdir added (-current only)\n"
"97/8/31 games setuid -> setgid.  Makes any games exploits benign (only\n"
"        score files vulnerable).  Please report any problems to\n"
"        eivind@FreeBSD.org (score-file ownership problems are known)\n"
"97/12/3 Add Intel's suggested fix for the F00F bug.  If you don't have\n"
"        a Pentium, the NO_F00F_HACK kernel option will disable it.\n"
"98/1/20 More robust protection against LAND attacks now incorporated.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:293
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The suidperl vulnerability mentioned in the CERT advisory CA-97.17 is\n"
"also believed to be fixed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:295
#, no-wrap
msgid "KerberosIV is now merged.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:307
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.3. USERLAND CHANGES\n"
"---------------------\n"
"The default binary type (and compiler toolchain) has been\n"
"switched from a.out to ELF.  This gives us access to much\n"
"newer compiler technology (much of which didn't support a.out),\n"
"allows for smaller executables and provides much better\n"
"support for languages like C++, among many other advantages.\n"
"Older a.out libraries and binaries will, of course, continue to work\n"
"and provisions have been made for having both varieties installed if\n"
"and as necessary for transitional purposes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:310
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Perl4 has now been replaced by Perl5 as a standard part of the\n"
"system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The default username length has increased to 16 characters.\n"
"Caution:  Old utmp/wtmp files will NOT work with this change since\n"
"the data records will be of the old size.  For a conversion utility\n"
"to aid with this, see /usr/src/tools/3.0-upgrade.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"/etc/sysconfig now replaced by more compact /etc/rc.conf file\n"
"[MERGED: Also in 2.2.1 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:322
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"fdisk(8) now numbers disk slices from 1 to 4 rather than from 0 to 3.\n"
"This brings it in line with the numbers used in the device names\n"
"in /dev.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:327
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Amd automounter has been updated from the 1993 4.4BSD version to\n"
"the latest current version of am-utils.  Map options have changed\n"
"somewhat, and a new configuration file, /etc/amd.conf, is supported.\n"
"See ``man 5 amd.conf''.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The ``picobsd'' package for creating custom FreeBSD boot floppies\n"
"and \"mini systems\" has been brought into /usr/src/release/picobsd.\n"
"See file:/usr/src/release/picobsd/README.html for further information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:338
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When operating over the network, finger(1) no longer closes the socket\n"
"immediately after sending its request, but instead waits for the\n"
"remote end to close first.  (The specification is ambiguous, so we are\n"
"following the behavior which interoperates with the most servers.)\n"
"This means that it is now possible to use the MIT directory and finger\n"
"people at certain broken Linux machines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:342
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There is a new flag to fetch(1) which allows it to talk to certain\n"
"broken HTTP implementations which react badly to a request message\n"
"immediately followed by a close of the connection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:345
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"netstat(1) now uses sysctl(3) to retrieve more statistics groups and\n"
"uses the correct, unsigned format for printing most of them out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:349
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A new VGA library (/usr/src/lib/libvgl) now exists for doing simple\n"
"VGA graphics to syscons ttys (sort of like Linux's libSVGA).\n"
"[MERGED: Also in 2.2.5 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:352
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xntpd's syslogging has been moved out into a facility of its own\n"
"(LOG_NTP, userland name \"ntp\").\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:358
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A new pair of ioctl's has been added: SIOC[SG]IFGENERIC.  The intent\n"
"is to provide for a hook to pass arbitrary ioctl subcommands down to a\n"
"network interface driver.  This is for example necesseray for PPP\n"
"drivers to communicate things like CHAP names and secrets, or variable\n"
"options between the driver and a userland utility.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:366
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sppp(4) has been improved a fair bit since FreeBSD 2.2.X.  It now\n"
"employs a full-fledged PPP state machine, offers a lot more of LCP and\n"
"IPCP negotiation, making it ready for dial-on-demand connections (like\n"
"those that are often running over ISDN).  It also offers PAP or CHAP\n"
"authentication.  The userland counterpart spppcontrol(8) is also the\n"
"first program that utilizes the abovementioned SIOC[SG]IFGENERIC ioctl\n"
"commands.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:372
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"moused(8) has been modified to support various mice with a ``wheel''.\n"
"It also automatically recognizes mice which support the PnP COM device\n"
"standard, so that the user is no longer required to supply a mouse\n"
"protocol type on the command line.\n"
"[MERGED: Also in 2.2.6 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:377
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ppp(8) supports many additional features including the PPP Multilink\n"
"Protocol (rfc1990), PPP Callback (with CBCP extensions) and client\n"
"side DNS negotiation.  Refer to the README.changes file in the source\n"
"directory for details of possible configuration conflicts.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Pthread read/write locks as defined by the Single UNIX Specification,\n"
"Version 2, have been added to the POSIX threads library, libc_r.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:383
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"System files are now owned by user `root', group `wheel'.  UID 0 is far\n"
"more protected than `bin'.  Especially over NFS.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:388
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"/bin/sh signal and trap handling reworked. Among other things, this\n"
"makes tty-mode emacs work when called from system(2), i.e. by a mail\n"
"agent. Several syntax bugs have been fixed.\n"
"[MERGED: Also in 2.2.8 and later releases on 2.2-STABLE branch]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/en/releases/3.0R/notes.adoc:394
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
